\series bold
PhD Thesis (September 2028)
\series default
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Summary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The phased structure of this research ensures both theoretical rigour and practical relevance.
 By advancing from basic single-agent simulation to full-fleet deployment in simulated and physical settings,
 the project is designed to produce a generalisable and robust approach to risk-aware planning in heterogeneous robot teams.
 The resulting contributions are expected to address key gaps in autonomous navigation under uncertainty and help pave the way for future robotic systems capable of operating safely and efficiently in real-world disaster response,
 exploration,
 and infrastructure monitoring scenarios.
\end_layout

